not only represents the lowest rung of the ladder, it also prov=\r\nides a ground for the upward swing of the Yuga cycle.\n\n  Similarly, Physica=\r\nl plane being lowest, provides force and ground for the upward movement of =\r\nsoul towards finer planes of existence.\n\n  Both the Yuga Cycles and Planes =\r\nof Existence are the manifestations of Nature, which implies that there is =\r\nmore or less an equal distribution of Pros and Cons factors associated with=\r\n each of them at every level.\n\n  Thus, Physical plane of existence is not a=\r\n disadvantageous place to realize the Brahman compared to the Mental planes=\r\n of existence.\n  Similarly, divinizing Physical body is not more disadvanta=\r\ngeous than divinizing Mind.\n\n  OTOH, it is even more, towards the core thin=\r\ng, to teach the sense of infinite existence to Matter than Mind.\n  Satva-Gu=\r\nna Mind is easily conquerable by Jnana.\n  When the Tamo-Guna, Matter, is co=\r\nnquered, by Iccha Shakti, what more is left there to conquer?\n\n  Also, it c=\r\nan be noted that when avatars like Rama face difficulties in Physical body,=\r\n like being hit by shakti in the war, the only great remedy is to conquer T=\r\namo-Guna itself like Mahaavatar Babaji has done.\n\nregards,\nAryama\n\n--- In v=\r\nedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com, Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@...&gt; wrote:\n&gt;\n&gt; Namaste=\r\n Sir,\n&gt;  \n&gt; &gt; Where is the fascination for what one already has ?\n&gt;  \n&gt; The=\r\n fascination is not &quot;for what one already has&quot;, but for resisting changes i=\r\nn that physical form with time based on the natural order (niyati)!\n&gt;  \n&gt; S=\r\ntriving for physical immortality as a great ideal can create such an unheal=\r\nthy fascination that is not idealized in any scriptures.\n&gt;  \n&gt; All scriptur=\r\nes, whether it is Upanishads or Yoga Vaasishtham, say that you overcome you=\r\nr self-identification with the perishable body and identify with that which=\r\n cannot be dest